**Baseline:**  758b44dab552f31b378874b5bf4c0609bfef6f5d

Bazel 6.3.0 is a minor LTS release. It is fully backward compatible with Bazel 6.0 and contains selected changes by the Bazel community and Google engineers.

## Highlights
* The new bazel mod command allows users to inspect their external dependency graph in Bzlmod. See [documentation](https://bazel.build/versions/6.3.0/external/mod-command) for details.
* Full lockfile support has been added to Bzlmod and is now enabled by default. See [documentation](https://bazel.build/versions/6.3.0/external/lockfile) for details.

## General
* Options specified on the pseudo-command `common` in `.rc` files are now ignored by commands that do not support them as long as they are valid options for *any* Bazel command. Previously, commands that did not support all options given for `common` would fail to run. These previous semantics of `common` are now available via the new `always` pseudo-command. ([#18609](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18609))
* Improve error on invalid `-//foo` and `-@repo//foo` options ([#18516](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18516))
* Adjust `--top_level_targets_for_symlinks`: `bazel-bin`, `bazel-testlogs`, etc. no longer mysteriously disappear ([#18916](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18916))
* Fix Xcode 14.3 compatibility ([#18490](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18490))
* Remove option to disable `ForkJoinPool`. ([#18791](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18791))

## Android
* Fix D8 dex merger failure when a synthetic class is placed on a different shard than its container class ([#16368](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/16368))
* Add a new provider for injecting native libs in android_binary for android_binary Starlarkification ([#18753](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18753))
* Add a new provider for passing dex related artifacts in android_binary for android_binary Starlarkification ([#18899](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18899))

## Build Event Protocol
* Add ActionCacheStatistics to BEP ([#18914](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18914))

## C++ / Objective-C
* Make cpp file extensions case sensitive again ([#18552](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18552))
* Add changes to cc_shared_library from head to 6.3 ([#18606](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18606))
* Make grep_includes optional inside cc_common.register_linkstamp_compile_action ([#18823](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18823))
* Add implementation deps support for Objective-C ([#18372](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18372))
* Add external_include_paths feature on Windows toolchain ([#18654](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18654))
* Additional source inputs can now be specified for compilation in cc_library targets using the additional_compiler_inputs attribute, and these inputs can be used in the $(location) function. ([#18882](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18882))
* Fix VS 2022 autodetection ([#18960](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18960))

## Coverage
* Expose metadata_files parameter in coverage_common.instrumented_files_info ([#18838](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18838))
* Check if json.gz files exist, not the gcov version. ([#18889](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18889))
* Add flag `--experimental_collect_code_coverage_for_generated_files` to enable coverage collection for generated files. ([#18664](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18664))
* Fix split post-processing of LLVM-based coverage ([#18737](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18737))

## External Dependencies / Bzlmod
* Overrides specified by non-root modules no longer cause an error, and are silently ignored instead. ([#18388](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18388))
* The --credential_helper flag is now stable, and works for repo fetching.
* Module extension usages can now be specified to be _isolated_. Each isolated usage causes a separate evaluation of the extension. See [documentation](https://bazel.build/versions/6.3.0/rules/lib/globals#use_extension.isolate) for more details.
* Report percentual download progress in repository rules ([#18471](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18471))
* Ignore hash string casing ([#18414](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18414))
* Include actual MODULE.bazel location in stack traces ([#18612](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18612))
* Fix WORKSPACE toolchain resolution with `--enable_bzlmod` ([#18649](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18649))
* The REPO.bazel and MODULE.bazel files are now also considered as workspace boundary markers. ([#18787](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18787))
* Yanked module versions no longer contribute dependency requirements or emit DEBUG messages for print() statements ([#18908](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18908))
* Report dev/non-dev deps imported via non-dev/dev usages ([#18922](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18922))
* Identify isolated extensions by exported name ([#18923](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18923))

## Java
* Pass version to java_runtimes created by local_java_repository ([#18415](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18415))
* Teach ijar about dynamic constants ([#18729](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18729))
* Update to latest turbine version ([#18803](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18803))
* Update Error Prone to 2.20.0 ([#18885](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18885))
* Update java_tools to v12.5 ([#18868](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18868))
* Disable UseCorrectAssertInTests by default ([#18948](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18948))

## Local Execution
* Use local_termination_grace_seconds when testing LinuxSandbox availability ([#18568](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18568))

## Query
* Add jsonproto option to query --output flag ([#18438](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18438))
* query --output=proto --order_output=deps now returns targets in topological order (previously there was no ordering). ([#18870](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18870))

## Remote Execution
* Prevent CredentialHelperEnvironment crash when invoking Bazel outside of a workspace. ([#18430](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18430))
* Use wall-time for credential helper invalidation ([#18413](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18413))
* Move credential helper setup into remote_helpers.sh so it can be reused by other shell tests. ([#18453](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18453))
* Support remote symlink outputs when building without the bytes. ([#18476](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18476))
* Enrich local BEP upload errors with file path and digest possible. ([#18481](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18481))
* Extend the credential helper default timeout to 10s. ([#18527](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18527))
* Ignore all errors when writing to stdin of a credential helper.([#18540](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18540))
* Implement failure circuit breaker ([#18541](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18541))
* Add ServerCapabilities into RemoteExecutionClient ([#18442](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18442))
* RemoteExecutionService: support output_symlinks in ActionResult ([#18441](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18441))
* RemoteExecutionService: Action.Command to set output_paths ([#18440](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18440))
* Add `ActionExecutionMetadata` as a parameter to `ActionInputPrefetcher#prefetchFiles`. ([#18656](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18656))
* Use failure_rate instead of failure count for circuit breaker  ([#18559](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18559))
* Update ignored_error logic for circuit_breaker ([#18662](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18662))
* Don't rewind the build if invocation id stays the same ([#18670](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18670))
* Fix potential memory leak in UI when BwoB. ([#18659](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18659))
* Properly handle invalid credential files ([#18779](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18779))
* Report remote execution messages as events ([#18780](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18780))
* Wait for outputs downloads before emitting local BEP events that reference these outputs. ([#18815](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18815))
* Fix non-declared symlink issue for local actions when BwoB. ([#18817](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18817))
* Download directory output for test actions ([#18846](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18846))

## Starlark / Build Language
* Perform builtins injection for WORKSPACE-loaded bzl files. ([#18819](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18819))

## Testing
* Fix test setup script to convey test exit code correctly ([#18514](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18514))
* Set `GTEST_SHARD_STATUS_FILE` in test setup ([#18482](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18482))
* Actually check if `TEST_SHARD_STATUS_FILE` has been touched ([#18418](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18418))
* test-setup.sh: Attempt to raise the original signal once more ([#18932](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18932))

## Acknowledgements

This release contains contributions from many people at Google, as well as amishra-u, Andreas Herrmann, Andy Hamon, andyrinne12, Benjamin Lee, Benjamin Peterson, Brentley Jones, Chirag Ramani, Christopher Rydell, Daniel Wagner-Hall, Ed Schouten, Fabian Brandstetter, Fabian Meumertzheim, Greg, Ivan Golub, Jon Landis, Kai Zhang, Keith Smiley, lripoche, Rasrack, Son Luong Ngoc, Takeo Sawada, Vertexwahn, Yannic.

body:
# Release 7.0.0-pre.20230504.4 (2023-05-23)

Baseline: b384a98a55e1ff4da0a650f5f782645581173358

Cherry picks:

   + c7792e87a855b7c831f571e8d90b74ddf0168cb7:
     Fix a bug that outputs from aspects are not downloaded.
   + 7705793ff3f6ea172fe01bbacb7ccc515150c4f7:
     Fix merge (#18452)
   + 2acbe305e3082afe4aa4c34850c8aa931f65d7fd:
     Release 7.0.0-pre.20230504.4 (2023-05-19)

Incompatible changes:

  - This has the side effect of changing the message on unsuccessful
    builds from
    ```
    FAILED: Build did NOT complete successfully (0 packages loaded)
    ```
    to
    ```
    ERROR: Build did NOT complete successfully
    ```
  - Bazel no longer increases the delay between progress updates when
    there is no cursor control.
  - This has the side effect of changing the message on unsuccessful
    builds from
    ```
    FAILED: Build did NOT complete successfully (0 packages loaded)
    ```
    to
    ```
    ERROR: Build did NOT complete successfully
    ```
  - the --experimental_async_execution flag is now a no-op.
  - --experimental_replay_action_out_err is not a no-op.
  - `cquery --output=files` also outputs source files.
  - `--incompatible_strict_conflict_checks` is flipped to true. See
    https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/16729 for details.
  - `--incompatible_strict_conflict_checks` is flipped to true. See
    https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/16729 for details.
  - `--incompatible_always_include_files_in_data` is flipped to true.
    See https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/16654 for details.
  - This changes the behavior of Python version in exec/host
    configuration. Mitigation is to set Python version on the targets.
  - When multiple --deleted_packages options are passed on the
    command line, they will be concatenated instead of the latest one
    taking effect.
  - This has the side effect of changing the message on unsuccessful
    builds from
  - JSON profile: Use doubles instead of strings for counter series.
  - query --output=proto --order_output=deps now returns targets in
    topological order (previously there was no ordering).
  - --experimental_build_transitive_python_runfiles is flipped to
    false. See #16303 for details
  - --incompatible_python_disable_py2 is flipped to true. See #17293
    for details.
  - When remote cache evicts blobs, Bazel will exit with code 39.
  - `--features` only applies to targets built in the target
    configuration, and `--host_features` is used for the host / exec
    configuration (gated behind `--incompatible_use_host_features`)
  - `--incompatible_strict_conflict_checks` is flipped to true. See
    https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/16729 for details.
  - Bazel's local CPU resource on Linux is now container aware. Use
    `--local_cpu_resources`, `--loading_phase_threads` or `--jobs` to
    override.
  - `copy_from_rule` is exec_groups is deprecated
    (https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/17668).
  - --legacy_bazel_java_test is now a no-op
  - --legacy_bazel_java_test is now a no-op
  - --legacy_bazel_java_test is now a no-op
  - `--experimental_execution_graph_log` no longer exists. Current
    users that want local logs need to pass
    `--experimental_enable_execution_graph_log
    --experimental_execution_graph_log_path=/some/local/path`.
    Current users that want logs uploaded to BEP need to pass
    `--experimental_enable_execution_graph_log
    --experimental_stream_log_file_uploads`.
  - Remove 'darwin' as a CPU value, use 'darwin_x86_64' instead
  - Remove high priority workers functionality from blaze.
  - Renamed PackageMetrics proto message to PackageLoadMetrics. The
    formats should be wire compatible.

New features:

  - The `aquery` and `cquery` commands now respect the
    `--query_file` flag just like the `query` command.
  - --experimental_repository_disable_download is now promoted to
    stable and is also available under the name
    --repository_disable_download .

Important changes:

  - The new path variable `$(rlocationpath ...)` and its plural form
    `$(rlocationpaths ...)` can be used to expand labels to the paths
    accepted by the `Rlocation` function of runfiles libraries. This
    is the preferred way to access data dependencies at runtime and
    works on all platforms, even when runfiles are not enabled (e.g.,
    on Windows by default).
  - Starlark `print()` statements are now emitted iff the line of
    code is executed. They are no longer replayed on subsequent
    invocations unless the Starlark code is re-executed.
    Additionally, multiple identical `print()` statements (same
    string from the same line of code, e.g. from a loop) are all
    emitted and no longer deduplicated.
  - Fixes a bug where some compilation flags would not be applied to
    a cc_test
  - removed outdated ctx.host_fragments
  - removed outdated ctx.host_configuration
  - Now that the host configuration is finished, `genrule` should
    prefer the use of `tools` and stop using `exec_tools`.
  - Added a `native.package_relative_label()` function, which
    converts a label string to a Label object in the context of the
    calling package, in contrast to `Label()`, which does so in the
    context of the current .bzl file. Both functions now also accept
    relative labels such as `:foo`, and are idempotent.
  - Update Android manifest merger to v30.1.3, and also drop support
    for legacy (pre-D8) desugaring.
  - Adds coverage metric support to android_local_test
  - Correctly encode double value positive infinity as "inf" instead
    of "+inf" for textprotos.
  - Add --use_target_platform_for_tests which uses the target
    platform for executing tests instead of the execution platform.
  - Custom C++ rules on Windows calling
    cc_common.create_linking_context_from_compilation_outputs should
    review whether each target of the rule type should produce a
    dynamic library since a condition which blocked their creation
    has been moved to the rules from behind the API.
  - Add flag `--experimental_remote_cache_ttl` and set the default
    value to 3 hours.
  - making --incompatible_use_platforms_repo_for_constraints do
    nothing. Using constraints from @bazel_tools//platforms with or
    without the flag will throw error with message "Constraints from
    @bazel_tools//platforms have been removed. Please use constraints
    from @platforms repository embedded in Bazel, or preferably
    declare dependency on https://github.com/bazelbuild/platforms"
  - Fixed an issue where WORKSPACE and WORKSPACE-loaded .bzl files
    couldn't see the Bzlmod root module's mappings when Bzlmod is
    enabled.
  - Subsequent settings of --extra_execution_platforms now override
    previous settings, instead of adding them to a list. If you
    currently set --extra_execution_platforms more than once, please
    migrate by passing a list of values to
    --extra_execution_platforms instead so that earlier values aren't
    overwritten.
  - @bazel_tools//config:common_settings.bzl has been removed.
    Use @bazel_skylib//rules:common_settings.bzl instead.
  - cc_shared_library is no longer experimental, see
    https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/16709 for details
  - The flag `--distinct_host_configuration` is removed. It has been
    a no-op since Bazel 6.0.0.
  - Added `native.module_name()` and `native.module_version()` to
    allow BUILD macro authors to acquire information about which
    Bazel module the current repo is associated with.
  - Add `--skip_incompatible_explicit_targets` option
  - Remove 'darwin' as a CPU value, use 'darwin_x86_64' instead
  - cc_test can now be configured by using a native.toolchain().
  - `@foo` labels can now be used on the command line as the
    top-level target (that is, `bazel build @foo` now works).
    Double-dot syntax is now forbidden (`bazel build ../foo` will no
    longer work).
  - The location of rules that explicitly specify `generator_name`
    and/or `generator_function` attributes (typically because they
    are incidentally copied from `native.existing_rule()`) is now the
    top-level call in the `BUILD` file, which is consistent with
    rules that do not explicitly specify these attributes.
  - Warnings (most notably those associated with the `deprecation`
    rule attribute) are no longer replayed on subsequent invocations
    unless the target in question is re-analyzed. Warnings are purely
    informational, so this change has no bearing on the correctness
    of the build. Downstream tests that break due to this change
    should update their expectations.
  - `--experimental_remote_build_event_upload` has been renamed to
    `--remote_build_event_upload`
  - [Breaking change] platform, constraint_setting, and
    constraint_value can no longer take an applicable_licenses value.
    Remediation is to remove the attribute and rely on the package
    level default.

    workspace boundary markers.

    `bazel_dep` directive, which allows version selection to upgrade
    a dependency up to the specified compatibility level.

    `--remote_grpc_log`

    if this parameter is specified and decoding fails, json.decode
    will return

    transitive dependency graph working together; but we've deemed
    that infeasible (and even if it was, it'd be so complicated and

Bazel 6.2.0 is a minor LTS release. It is fully backward compatible with Bazel 6.0 and contains selected changes by the Bazel community and Google engineers.

## Highlights
* Added preliminary support for a lockfile for Bzlmod. It's disabled by default; use `--lockfile_mode=update` to enable it. Check flag documentation [here](https://bazel.build/reference/command-line-reference#flag--lockfile_mode). This lockfile contains only Bazel module information; it does not involve module extensions. ([#18143](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18143))

## General
* `@foo` labels can now be used on the command line as the top-level target (that is, `bazel build @foo` now works). Double-dot syntax is now forbidden (`bazel build ../foo` will no longer work). ([#17945](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17945))
* The aquery and cquery commands now respect the --query_file flag just like the query command. ([#17823](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17823))
* Patch zlib to fix compatibility with latest Xcode ([#18000](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18000))
* profile: add profile_finish_ts ([#18129](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18129))
* Use ctime in file digest cache key ([#18105](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18105))
* Include cause when reporting `ActionExecutionException` ([#18185](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18185))
* Check for the nullness of `AspectValue`. ([#18186](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18186))
* Force the Bazel server Java runtime to use the root locale ([#17733](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17733))
* Fix message generation of `ActionExecutionException` ([#18257](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18257))

## Android
* Added coverage metric support to android_local_test ([#17467](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17467))
* Include build-tools/X.Y.Z/{lib,lib64}/** in the minimal set of SDK files used by the Android integration tests. ([#17826](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17826))
* Fix worker and multiplex workers for DexBuilder and Desugar actions ([#17965](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17965))

## C++ / Objective-C
* Fix wasm dynamic library extension crash ([#17765](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17765))
* Enable C++ deps pruning on Windows when PARSE_SHOWINCLUDES is available. ([#17957](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17957))
* Add attribute provides = [CcInfo] to _cc_proto_aspect ([#17979](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17979))
* Expose cc_proto_aspect as a top level symbol. ([#17980](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17980))

## CLI
* Handle `SIGWINCH` under `bazel run //some:test` (i.e. test rules) correctly. ([#17760](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17760))
* Use less subshells and `tee`s in running tests with `bazel run`. ([#17869](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17869))

## Configurability
* Allow multiple matching select branches if they resolve to the same value ([#18066](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18066))
* cquery --output-starlark: better alias support ([#17786](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17786))
* Fix crashes on select()able target_compatible_with attributes. ([#18135](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18135))
* Add "did you mean?" suggestions for typoed rule attribute names ([#17855](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17855))
* Turn applicable_licenses on platform() into a no-op. ([#18089](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18089))

## External Dependencies
* Added `native.module_name()` and `native.module_version()` to allow BUILD macro authors to acquire information about which Bazel module the current repo is associated with. ([#17893](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17893))
* Added a new `max_compatibility_level` attribute to the `bazel_dep` directive, which allows version selection to upgrade a dependency up to the specified compatibility level. ([#18178](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18178))
* Added `module_ctx.is_dev_dependency`, allowing an extension to see whether a tag is specified to be a dev dependency. ([#17934](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17934))
* Added `module_ctx.extension_metadata`, allowing the extension to specify the list of repos the root module can `use_repo` on. If the root module violates this list, Bazel will print out a Buildozer command to automatically fix the use_repo directive. ([#18174](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18174))
* Fixed an issue where WORKSPACE and WORKSPACE-loaded .bzl files couldn't see the Bzlmod root module's mappings when Bzlmod is enabled. ([#17818](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17818))
* Added suggestions to invalid tag class errors. ([#17896](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17896))
* Workspace relative paths are now supported in --override_module. ([#17906](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17906))
* Fail early if `use_extension` has a bad label ([#17926](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17926))
* Added `dev_dependency` to `register_{execution_platforms,toolchains}`. ([#18259](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18259))

## Java
* Silence setlocale warnings in Java stub ([#17741](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17741))
* Split darwin java_tools to x86_64 and arm64 ([#18197](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18197))
* Upgrade Azul JDK 17 archives. ([#17852](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17852))
* Add version to JavaRuntimeInfo ([#17913](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17913))
* Update default_java_toolchain.bzl to fix a regression ([#18225](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18225))
* Updated java_tools to v12.3 to fix BazelTestRunner compatibility with jre8 ([#18328](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18328))

## Python
* Removed temporary module space created for zip-based binaries ([#17764](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17764))
* Set envvar for runfiles manifest, not runfiles dir, when using a manifest ([#18133](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18133))

## Remote Execution
* Skip empty directories instead of throwing in the prefetcher. ([#17718](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17718))
* Remove actionId from `RemoteFileArtifactValue`. ([#17724](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17724))
* Correctly handle templated tree artifacts in the prefetcher. ([#17735](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17735))
* [credentialhelper] Ignore failing to provide request ([#17745](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17745))
* [remote] upload: treat `ALREADY_EXISTS` as success ([#17732](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17732))
* Fix data race in prefetcher. ([#17744](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17744))
* Clear all remote metadata if any of them are evicted from remote cache ([#17770](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17770))
* Fix seeking of empty chunkers. ([#17830](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17830))
* Rework ByteStreamUploader early return logic. ([#17832](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17832))
* Avoid unnecessary copying when building Merkle trees. ([#17930](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17930))
* Cache Merkle trees for tree artifacts. ([#17998](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17998))
* Deduplicate concurrent computations of the same Merkle tree. ([#18015](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18015))
* Add exception message to 'failed to create output directory' ([#18067](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18067))
* Prevent failures creating output directories ([#18062](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18062))
* Gracefully handle output symlinks with BwoB ([#18106](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18106))
* Automatically retry the build if encountered remote cache eviction error ([#18171](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18171))
* Allow remote retry max delay to be user configurable ([#18061](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18061))
* Rename --experimental_remote_grpc_log to --remote_grpc_log ([#18193](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18193))
* Construct TreeArtifactValues on multiple threads. ([#18194](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18194))
* Fix crash on multiple output symlinks with BwoB ([#18226](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/18226))

## Starlark / Build Language
* Relax JSON parser, ensure duplicate keys are overridden ([#17868](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17868))

Bazel 6.1.0 is a minor LTS release. It is fully backward compatible with Bazel 6.0 and contains selected changes by the Bazel community and Google engineers.

## General
* Do not count tests as failed that have not started ([#17269](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17269))
* Add an `--incompatible_strict_conflict_checks` alias for `--experimental_strict_conflict_checks`. ([#17589](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17589))
* Rerun the artifact conflict check when --incompatible_strict_conflict_checks changes. ([#17592](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17592))
* Add exec transition to Java version of `py_test` ([#17594](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17594))

## Android
* Multiplex worker fixes and tests for Android busybox tools ([#17371](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17371))
* Make desugar dependencies deterministic ([#17217](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17217))

## Apple / Xcode
* Allow the timeout value for execute calls on a mac to be set via an environment variable

## C++ / Objective-C
* Use `xcrun` to invoke `install_name_tool` ([#17253](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17253))
* Add sanitizer features to `unix_cc_toolchain_config` ([#17263](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17263))
* Rulesets can start using the new optional form of `find_cpp_toolchain` now and benefit from the toolchain actually being optional once that has been implemented in a future version of Bazel. ([#17331](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17331))
* Enable `archive_param_file` feature by default for Windows ([#17344](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17344))
* Only try to create groups of test actions in the ui. ([#17343](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17343))
* Find `libtool` when using `BAZEL_USE_CPP_ONLY_TOOLCHAIN`. ([#17327](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17327))
* Add `-dead_strip` in default opt link flags for darwin ([#17312](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17312))
* Fix a `cc_binary` bug for `cc_shared_library` on Windows which prevented `cc_shared_librarys` from working across packages ([#17445](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17445))
* Remove O1 from sanitizer feature flag defaults ([#17439](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17439))
* Allow -v to libtool ([#17459](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17459))
* Fix RPATHs for cc toolchain solib when sibling layout is used ([#17506](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17506))
* Add `--host_features` flag ([#17528](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17528))
* Only fetch `@remote_coverage_tools` when collecting coverage ([#17512](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17512), [#17287](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17287))
* Bump minimum supported macOS versions to 10.13 ([#17570](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17570))
* Allow `.wasm` cc executable and dynamic library extension ([#17440](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17440))

## Configurability
* Do not clear `--platforms` on no-op change to `--cpu` ([#17273](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17273))
* Set `--experimental_action_listeners` to default in `exec` config ([#17284](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17284))
* Fix Bazel 6.0 crash regression when incompatible target skipping mixes with `--auto_cpu_environment_group` ([#17613](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17613))

## Coverage
* Emit LLVM coverage for source file paths with a `tmp` segment ([#17324](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17324))

## External Dependencies
* Fix `git_repository` with the latest version of Git. ([#17247](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17247))
* Add `SpellChecker` suggestions for common Bzlmod errors ([#17216](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17216))
* Accept tildes in `--override_module` ([#17313](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17313))
* Test and fix root symlink edge case in runfiles library ([#17365](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17365))
* Fix Bash `runfiles_current_repository` for tools ([#17329](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17329))
* Fix label unambiguous canonical form to correctly report non-visible repo names ([#17326](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17326))
* Prettify labels in action progress messages with Bzlmod ([#17278](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17278))
* Do not recommend `shallow_since` for `git_repository` ([#17356](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17356))
* Bump version number in runfiles.bash init code ([#17539](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17539))
* Properly report repo fetch progress during main repo mapping computation ([#17544](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17544))

## Java
* Register JavaCompileActionContext in Bazel ([#17325](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17325))
* Fix Java coverage collection with Java 8 runtime ([#17491](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17491))
* Make AutoBazelRepositoryProcessor compatible with Java 8 ([#17504](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17504))

## Local Execution
* Added support for user-specified resource types in the resource manager. The available amount of extra resources can be specified using the new `--local_extra_resources=<resourcename>=<amount>` command line flag, which is analogous to the existing `--local_cpu_resources` and `--local_memory_resources` flags. ([#17229](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17229))
* Allow Java coverage collection for external targets. ([#17360](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17360))
* Add support for wrapping system streams in `WorkRequestHandler` ([#17583](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17583))

## Remote Execution
* Fix an issue where some intermediate outputs are downloaded with minimal mode when doing `bazel test` ([#17234](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17234))
* Make download progress not jumpy by always emitting trailing zero ([#17290](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17290))
* Upload all logs in BEP even with minimal upload ([#17299](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17299))
* Do the AC integrity check for disk part of the combined cache.([#17309](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17309))
* Improve BES uploader performance by not querying remote cache but always using bytestream protocol ([#17352](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17352))
* Improve error message for concurrent modifications ([#17396](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17396))
* Make bazel coverage work with minimal mode ([#17397](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17397))
* Make Bazel more responsive and use less memory when `--jobs` is high ([#17398](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17398))
* Remove usage of gRPC Context cancellation in the remote execution client. ([#17438](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17438))
* Reduce flakiness on Windows for BwoB tests ([#17513](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17513))
* Exit with code 39 if remote cache evicted blobs that Bazel need during an invocation ([#17496](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17496))
* Fix symlink file creation overhead ([#17488](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17488))
* Allow following builds to continue when remote cache evicted files ([#17538](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17538), [#17601](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17601), [#17605](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17605))
* Report background downloads for BwoB ([#17619](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17619))
* Add flag `--experimental_writable_outputs` to allow Bazel generate writable outputs ([#17617](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17617))

## Starlark / Build Language
* Allow `map_each` to return `None` in `TemplateDict#add_joined` ([#17288](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17288))
* Allow `TemplateDict#map_each` callback to return a list of strings ([#17306](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17306))
* Added `native.package_relative_label` function ([#17435](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/17435))
